description: Long overlooked, the question of military mobility has returned to the forefront of Western priorities in response to the Russian threat. headline: Sudan: Humanitarian crisis from Darfur war spills over into Chad
description: For more than 20 years, N'Djamena has endured the consequences of the Sudanese conflict, hosting over one million refugees. Chad has also acted as a backer of armed groups when it suits its interests, risking internal destabilization.

headline: Designer Pieter Mulier writes a new chapter in Alaïa's history
description: After four years as creative director of the couturehouse founded by Azzedine Alaïa, the Belgian designer has just won the International Designer of the Year award at the CFDA Awards in New York. A few months ago, he moved into a modern building in the 11th arrondissement, ushering the brand into a new era.
